You have made the land tremble; you have torn it apart;
\q heal its fissures, for it is shaking.
\q

6:
God has spoken in his holiness, "I will rejoice;
\q I will divide Shechem and apportion out the Valley of Succoth.
\q

7:
Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine;
\q Ephraim also is my helmet;
\q Judah is my scepter.

8:
Moab is my washbasin;
\q over Edom I will throw my shoe;
\q I will shout in triumph because of Philistia."
\q
